# Supporting Documents

Place supporting artefacts for each user story in a folder named after the story file.

## Convention

```
user_stories/
  apply_leave.txt          ← user story file
  apply_leave/             ← supporting docs for that story
    wireframe.pdf
    field_rules.xlsx
    api_schema.json
    acceptance_criteria.docx
```

When you run `phoenix generate --story-file user_stories/apply_leave.txt`, Phoenix
automatically discovers the `apply_leave/` folder and passes all documents to the
LLM so it can generate more accurate test cases and locators.

You can also point to any folder or file explicitly:

```bash
phoenix generate --story-file user_stories/apply_leave.txt --docs path/to/docs/
```

## Supported formats

| Format | Extension |
|--------|-----------|
| Text / Markdown | `.txt` `.md` |
| PDF | `.pdf` — requires `pip install pypdf` |
| Word | `.docx` — requires `pip install python-docx` |
| Excel | `.xlsx` `.xls` — requires `pip install openpyxl` |
| Data | `.csv` `.json` `.xml` `.yaml` |
| Web | `.html` `.htm` |

## What to put here

- Wireframes or design screenshots (exported as PDF)
- Acceptance criteria spreadsheets (CSV or XLSX)
- API or data schemas (JSON or XML)
- Business requirements documents (DOCX or PDF)
- Field validation rules (any format)

## What NOT to put here

- Sensitive credentials or secrets (use environment variables)
- Very large files — content is truncated at ~8 000 chars per document
- Domain-wide business context (put that in `domain_knowledge/` instead)
